import axios from 'axios'; const WeatherApp = () => { const fetchData = async () => { try { const cityInput = document.getElementById('search'); const city = cityInput.value; const response = await axios.get(`http://localhost:3007/api/weather?city=${city}`); console.log(response.data); // Now you can access the data in the response variable and do further processing const data = response.data; document.getElementById('top-degree').innerHTML = `${data.temperature}`; document.getElementById('sun').innerHTML = `${data.weatherDescription}`; document.getElementById('wind').innerHTML = "Wind: " + `${data.windSpeed}` + "mph"; document.getElementById('humidity').innerHTML = `${data.humidityCheck}`; } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching weather data:', error.message); } }; //fetchData(); return (
